        <div n="389-771L" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-389-771L-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-1"> Quoth King Robin our Ribbans I see are too few&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-2"> Of S<hi rend="sup">ṭ</hi> Andrew the Green &amp; S<hi rend="sup">ṭ</hi> George's the Blew.</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-3"> I must find out a Red One, /<hi rend="underline">hole</hi>/ Colour more gay,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-4"> Which will tye up my Subjects with pride to obey.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-5"> Thô the Chequer may suffer by prodigal Donors,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-6"> Yet the King's ne'er exhausted, that Fountain of Honours.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-7"> Men of more Wit than Money our Pensions will fitt,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-8"> But this will bribe those of more Money than Wit.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-9"> Who with Faith most implicit obey my Commands,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-10"> Thô as empty as Young, or as Saucy as Sands;</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-11"> Who will soonest leap over a Stick for the King,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-389-771L-line-12"> Shall be qualified best, for a Dog in a String.389-771L   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
